    "client_msg_id": "43d875ca-2dfb-4d0d-aa88-5261d39f9979",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "oh yeah, I have worked with json schema - I have even written an implementation of the latest spec (it is missing some features) (<https://github.com/opethe1st/PyJschema>) and passes the test suite they have. I think Jsonschema is too complicated and tries to do too many things, annotations, assertions, some keywords aren’t independent, recursiveRef and recursiveAnchor etc. + the spec can be a pain to read and get correct (turns out various implementation dont agree).",
